==English==

===Adjective===
'''scant'''
# very little, very few
#:  "After his previous escapades, Mary had '''scant''' reason to believe John."

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}
# Masonary: A block of stone sawn on two sides down to the bed level.
# Timber: A measurement of sawn wood. e.g. 2x4" scants.

